column5: I was outside most of the morning south east of Montreal....felt nothing.   It went around. It probably didn't want to knock over your bottles.
The horror!!!!  I was still asleep, I guess it wasn't enough to shake me awake.
In the retirement home I was at, some of the residents felt it. I didn't… insert your own punch line here_____________.
Heard the radio announcer freaking out when it happened. Noticed nada in West Niagara.
In Mattawa it was strongly felt,my trailer was just rocking.   vance
sitting online this morning here in St.Thomas  herd and felt 2 rumbles about 15-20 seconds apart....almost like a 18 wheel truck drove down my street,but there was no truck.
My brother in Toronto thought that someone had graciously paid off Mike Duffies $90,000  tab and that he was doing the HAPPY DANCE
I felt it in Markham.
~~~Butt too big to feel anythung
A conservative did that already.
I was on the water fishing  didn't  feel a thing,  but the lake trout kept biting
Yup... Didn't feel a thing out in the boat....
hmmmm.. that was the exact moment my mother-in-law rolled out of bed and hit the floor. Coincidence? I think not
so did she cause the earth quake or fell out of bed because of the quake  just checking    lol
you know Terry
It was felt here in Penetanguishene. We usually feel any earth quake which originates near Ottawa or South western Quebec.
NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!!!!!!!
Anyone feel that earthquake in Toronto?
Im at Bathurst and Lakeshore, didnt notice anything? When did this happen?
I'm at home with my daughter and we both looked at each other as the house shook!  Lasted about 20 seconds....rhythmic motion.
Like 5 minutes ago, St.Clair and Jane. everyone in the building felt it, about 100 employees... I could see my coffee wobbling on the table.
I'm at my internship on Bloor and Yonge, just felt it! Glad I'm not the only one.
Felt it in Peterborough.
Felt it in London too.
it was a magnitude 4.8 and felt all over southern ontario !!! the epicenter was breaside ontario !!!! nothing felt here in sunderland ontario,but lots of calls comming in to radio stations !!!!

Nothing in Milton?
Weird, we're having break and didnt feel anything
also felt it in peterborough. It shook 3 pictures off the wall
the epicenter was near anrprior !!! the ottawa valley,they get them all the time,maybe it will shake up them walleyes in the ottawa river for me....
Didn't feel it in Richmond Hill, but others in larger buildings are all out on the streets and in the parking lots around here.   Last time it was very noticeable!!
Hard to feel an earthquake when you ride an ATV for work....

Apparently a second one followed 10 minutes later.  Automatic detection of seismic event: magnitude 4.2 - 17 May 9:53 EDT - BRAESIDE, ON regionAutomatic detection of seismic event: magnitude 4.8 - 17 May 9:43 EDT - BRAESIDE, ON region  Source: http://www.earthquakescanada.nrcan.gc.ca/index-eng.php
I hope this doesn't affect the fishing this weekend
yes and they now said it was upgraded to a 5.1 magnitude !!!! and felt real hard in most of western quebec as well....awesome
I'm 15 miles north of Peterboro and have been working outside all morning and didn't feel a thing.
Didn't feel it, but I always miss them
Up to a 5.2 now
Didn't feel it in KW

Didn't feel a thing up here in the Valley way, way, way up North.... was listining to Disturbed while fishing for specks and limited out in 15 minutes LOL   even the bugs weren't quick enough to bite me LOL
Didn't feel it in KW
